(27, 1, '2009-11-17 14:03:04', '2009-11-17 14:03:04', 'I''ve just spent a lunch break getting a Wordpress site up and running for my blog. I was pleasantly surprised at how easy it is to set up. The Wordpress <a title="Wordpress installation instructions" href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Installing_WordPress#Famous_5-Minute_Install" target="_blank">Famous 5-Minute Install</a> documentation set it out very clearly.\r\n\r\nHere''s what I did:\r\n\r\nInstalled PHP on my development machine with IIS7 (probably the trickiest part)\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title="PHP documentation" href="http://www.php.net/manual/en/install.windows.iis7.php" target="_blank">Enable FastCGI support in IIS7</a></li>\r\n	<li>Created an IIS7 website, unzip Wordpress site there</li>\r\n	<li>Installed MySQL and MySQL Administrator (part of the MySQL Tools download) from <a title="MySQL Downloads" href="http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/" target="_blank">the MySQL site</a></li>\r\n	<li>Used MySQL Administrator to created a new MySQL database and a new user for that database</li>\r\n	<li>Edit wp-config.php in the Wordpress site<a title="wp-config.php settings" href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Installing_WordPress#Step_3:_Set_up_wp-config.php" target="_blank"> to point to your database</a></li>\r\n	<li>Browse to the installation page and it''s as easy as that</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNext, I created a MySQL database on my hosting provider and uploaded the website to the web server, changing the wp-config.php file to point to the new database.\r\n\r\nI did have to edit the database table wp_options to update the URL of the website because it was going to http://localhost when I tried to go to the admin pages.', 'Wordpress in a lunch break', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3-revision-3', '', '', '2009-11-17 14:03:04', '2009-11-17 14:03:04', '', 3, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2009/11/17/3-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(28, 1, '2010-02-27 21:46:46', '2010-02-27 21:46:46', '<p>I''ve just spent a lunch break getting a Wordpress site up and running for my blog. I was pleasantly surprised at how easy it is to set up. The Wordpress <a title="Wordpress installation instructions" href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Installing_WordPress#Famous_5-Minute_Install">Famous 5-Minute Install</a> documentation set it out very clearly.</p>\r\n<p>Here''s what I did:</p>\r\n<p>Installed PHP on my development machine with IIS7 (probably the trickiest part)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a title="PHP documentation" href="http://www.php.net/manual/en/install.windows.iis7.php" target="_blank">Enable FastCGI support in IIS7</a></li>\r\n<li>Created an IIS7 website, unzip Wordpress site there</li>\r\n<li>Installed MySQL and MySQL Administrator (part of the MySQL Tools download) from <a title="MySQL Downloads" href="http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/" target="_blank">the MySQL site</a></li>\r\n<li>Used MySQL Administrator to created a new MySQL database and a new user for that database</li>\r\n<li>Edit wp-config.php in the Wordpress site<a title="wp-config.php settings" href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Installing_WordPress#Step_3:_Set_up_wp-config.php" target="_blank"> to point to your database</a></li>\r\n<li>Browse to the installation page and it''s as easy as that</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Next, I created a MySQL database on my hosting provider and uploaded the website to the web server, changing the wp-config.php file to point to the new database.</p>\r\n<p>I did have to edit the database table wp_options to update the URL of the website because it was going to http://localhost when I tried to go to the admin pages.</p>\r\n', 'Wordpress in a lunch break', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3-revision-4', '', '', '2010-02-27 21:46:46', '2010-02-27 21:46:46', '', 3, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/02/27/3-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(29, 1, '2010-02-27 22:28:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'I spoke to a good friend of mine last week who told me his fiancee wanted to build a website and maybe try to get into web design or development.\r\n\r\nAs a web developer there was a huge amount of advice I wanted to give him there and then, and of course he was completely lost after the first 30 seconds!\r\n\r\nSo I''m going to make a list here of some of the most important things a starting-out web developer should know about.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Standards</li>\r\n	<li>Browser compatibility and testing</li>\r\n	<li>Firefox addons</li>\r\n	<li>Source control</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Web development tools', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2010-02-27 22:28:52', '2010-02-27 22:28:52', '', 0, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=29', 0, 'post', '', 0),
