nt-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 19px; white-space: normal;">\r\n</span></span></pre>\r\n<pre class="brush:csharp"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 19px; white-space: normal;">\r\n</span></span></pre>\r\n<pre class="brush:csharp"><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px; white-space: normal; font-size: 13px;">\r\n</span></pre>\r\nFor the PageFiles, Globals, and Documents folders, I''ve simply moved them into a folder above the root of the website and modified the physical paths. This is not an ideal solution as the path will change on different machines, but I''m going to live with it for now.\r\n<h2>Install the Public Templates</h2>\r\nI used the EPiServer deployment centre to do this. It needs your website to be set up in IIS before it can access it. Create a new IIS website pointing to your EPiServer site. Set the physical path to your site directory and set a host name (that you can put in your hosts file to access the site).\r\n\r\nStart the EPiServer DeploymentÂ CentreÂ and select "Install Public Templates". Select your website from the list and click install.\r\n\r\nThis should add a Templates directory to your website and add some pages to the database too.\r\n<h2 style="font-size: 1.5em;">Move assemblies</h2>\r\nAlso, move the referenced assemblies in the web project to a folder with your solution files so they can be checked in. Make sure you re-add the references to the projetc from the new location and set "Copy Local" to true.', 'Creating a new EPiServer 6 Solution', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '50-revision-12', '', '', '2010-04-19 17:41:52', '2010-04-19 16:41:52', '', 50, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/04/19/50-revision-12/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
