(81, 1, '2010-04-29 23:31:57', '2010-04-29 22:31:57', 'Well, I''m trying to learn Swedish at the moment and have endlessÂ pieces of paper listing SwedishÂ vocabulary, verbÂ conjugations, and phrases. So I''m planning to create a web app that can hold all these words and allow me to do interesting things with them, which will hopefully help me learn more Swedish.\n<h3>NHibernate</h3>\nI''m starting by following the NHibernate guide at http://nhforge.org/wikis/howtonh/your-first-nhibernate-based-application.aspx.\n\nI''ve downloaded NHibernate and created a solution with a class library projects for data, core domain, and tests.\n\nThe domain I have in mind is very basic (for now).Â  It consists of entities: Word, Translation, and Language.\n<ul>\n	<li>Copy the mapping file schema xsd file to the lib directory and reference it in Visual Studio</li>\n	<li>Creat e a mapping file for the entity Word in the data project</li>\n	<li>Add an id section, with generator set to identity</li>\n</ul>', 'Project: libretto - Step 1 - NHibernate', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '69-revision-2', '', '', '2010-04-29 23:31:57', '2010-04-29 22:31:57', '', 69, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/04/29/69-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(82, 1, '2010-04-28 10:34:39', '2010-04-28 09:34:39', '<pre class="brush:csharp">var minutesRegex = /\\d+(?=m)/;\r\nvar minutesMatch = minutesRegex.exec(timeString)\r\n\r\nif (minutesMatch) {\r\n	var minutes = minutesMatch[0];\r\n}</pre>\r\n<h3>The regular expression</h3>\r\n\\d matches any digit\r\n\r\n+ matches one or more\r\n\r\n(?=m) is a lookahead, it matches "m" but doesn''t include it in the result of the match\r\n\r\nIt will match "10" in the string "2h 10m 30s"\r\n<h3>References</h3>\r\n<a href="http://www.regular-expressions.info/javascript.html">http://www.regular-expressions.info/javascript.html</a>', 'Javascript Regex', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '75-revision-5', '', '', '2010-04-28 10:34:39', '2010-04-28 09:34:39', '', 75, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/04/28/75-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(83, 1, '2010-05-01 11:00:35', '2010-05-01 10:00:35', '<pre class="brush:csharp">var minutesRegex = /\\d+(?=m)/;\r\nvar minutesMatch = minutesRegex.exec(timeString)\r\n\r\nif (minutesMatch) {\r\n	var minutes = minutesMatch[0];\r\n}</pre>\r\n<h3>The regular expression</h3>\r\n\\d matches any digit\r\n\r\n+ matches one or more\r\n\r\n(?=m) is a zero-width positive lookahead, it matches "m" but doesn''t include it in the result of the match. eg. <tt>t(?=s)</tt>matches the secondÂ <tt>t</tt> inÂ <tt>streets (<a href="http://www.regular-expressions.info/refadv.html">http://www.regular-expressions.info/refadv.html</a>)</tt>.\r\n\r\nIt will match "10" in the string "2h 10m 30s"\r\n<h3>References</h3>\r\n<a href="http://www.regular-expressions.info/javascript.html">http://www.regular-expressions.info/javascript.html</a>', 'Javascript Regex', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '75-revision-6', '', '', '2010-05-01 11:00:35', '2010-05-01 10:00:35', '', 75, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/01/75-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
