(132, 1, '2010-06-11 14:09:19', '2010-06-11 13:09:19', 'I''m setting up a new project using N2 CMS but don''t have a clear procedure for downloading and setting up an N2 site. I''m going to use the MVC templates example site as a starting point so make sure you have ASP.NET MVC 2 installed.\n<h3>Downloading the Source</h3>\nEither get the latest release from CodePlex atÂ Â <a href="http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446">http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446</a> or get the svn repository url from the N2CMS page on Google Code atÂ <a href="http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/">http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/</a> and get the latest version.Â I prefer to get the svn version because it''s probably more up to date.Â Next, go to the "src"Â folder and run the batch file to build dependencies. Now open the MVC example solution in the folder "N2.Templates.Mvc"\n<h3>Some Build Errors...</h3>\nI got a few build errors related to missing N2 references so I just copied these into the bin folder from the src/wwwroot folder, andÂ referencedÂ them.\n<h3>Moving to a New Project</h3>\nNow I have the MVC example running I want to copy it to a new project folder and check it into a new source control repository. Copy theN2.Templates.MvcÂ folder from the "src" folder, Â you can use Beyond Compare so to filter out the .svn folders.\n\nI haveÂ rearrangedÂ the Â the folder structure for svn, adding trunk/branches folders, renamed wwwroot to Project.Site and added a lib folder for the project references, and an app folder for any supporting projects.Â Next, commit everything to a new svn repository, excluding the products of builds such as the bin older and contents.\nI''ve also renamed the solution and project files to match the project I''m working on, and also the assembly name and namespace for the project. Â You can use ReSharper to fix the namespaces in the source (right-click project, refactor, adjust namespaces), but you will also need to do a find and replace across the solution to make sure you change all instances of the old namespace.\nI also removed the namespace entries in the web.config system.web, pages, namespaces section because I like to seeÂ explicitÂ import statements, it''s helps me understand what''s going on. This does involve fixing the imports in pretty much every template though.\n<h3>Locking it down</h3>\nThe MVC templates site comes with a great selection of built in page types and parts, as well as example content. Obviously you need to change the example content to fit your project, but you should also disable page types and parts that are not required for the project. Although a client will happy take extra functionality, if you give it to them they''ll expect it to work the way they want it to and you''ll just create extra work for yourself. You can easily remove page types and parts using the N2 DisableAttribute on their class definition.\n<pre>[Disable]\npublic class FaqList : AbstractContentPage, IStructuralPage</pre>\n<h4>Themes</h4>\nIf you edit the start page in N2 you''ll see you can select a theme from a drop-down list, this is another feature I don''t need for this project (as it will only have one theme/design) so I''ve removed the property from StartPage.cs\n<pre>[EditableThemeSelection("Theme", 74, ContainerName = LayoutArea)]\npublic string Theme\n{\nget { return (string)(GetDetail("Theme") ?? string.Empty); }\nset { SetDetail("Theme", value); }\n}</pre>\nAnd also changed the Global.asax.cs to use the WebFormViewEngine instead of the ThemedMasterViewEngine:\n<pre>ViewEngines.Engines.Insert(0, new WebFormViewEngine());</pre>\n<h4>More things to remove</h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>The language menu from TopMenu.ascx</li>\n	<li>The site logo from Top.ascx</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Organising the styles</h3>\nTODO\n<h3>Configuring TinyMCE</h3>\nTODO\n<h3>Deployment Checklist</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>set checkInstallationStatus to false in web.config (&lt;installer checkInstallationStatus="false" /&gt;)</li>\n	<li>enable/disable globalization in web.config</li>\n	<li>set error reporting email address in web.config</li>\n</ul>\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">References</span>\n\n<a href="http://interferencelogik.com/docs/N2CMS_TheLittleHandbook.pdf">http://interferencelogik.com/docs/N2CMS_TheLittleHandbook.pdf</a>\n\n<a href="http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446">http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446</a>\n\n<a href="http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/">http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/</a>', 'Creating a new N2 CMS project', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '118-revision-3', '', '', '2010-06-11 14:09:19', '2010-06-11 13:09:19', '', 118, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/06/11/118-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
