g</h3>\r\n<strong>git merge [hash]</strong>\r\n\r\nMerge a commit from another branch.\r\n<div><strong>git checkout master</strong></div>\r\n<div><strong>git merge beta</strong></div>\r\n<div><strong>git push origin master</strong></div>\r\n<div>Merge beta branch into master branch</div>\r\n<h3>Working with Remotes</h3>\r\n<strong>git remote show [remote-name]</strong>\r\n\r\nGet the details of the remote repository, including branches.\r\n\r\n<strong>git remote</strong>\r\n\r\nLists your remote repositories.\r\n\r\n<strong>git fetch [remote-name]</strong>\r\n\r\nFetch changes from remote repository, but don''t update the working directory (use <strong>rebase </strong>for that).\r\n\r\n<strong>git pull [remote-name]</strong>\r\n\r\nFetch changes from remote repository and update the working directory.\r\n\r\n<strong>git push [remote-name] [branch-name]</strong>\r\n\r\nPush your local commits to a remote repository.\r\n\r\n<strong>Tricks</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>git update-index</strong> --assume-unchanged connectionString.config\r\n\r\nIgnore a tracked file\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Useful References</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://cheat.errtheblog.com/s/git">http://cheat.errtheblog.com/s/git</a>', 'Git Shortcuts', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '115-revision-7', '', '', '2010-06-10 12:14:44', '2010-06-10 11:14:44', '', 115, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/06/10/115-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(136, 1, '2010-05-14 16:58:38', '2010-05-14 15:58:38', '<div>MVC Controller Tests</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Test rendering of all views</li>\r\n	<li>Test reading entities from the repository into the model\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Test for when repositoryÂ returns null</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Creating entities\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check that all model values are passed to the repository method</li>\r\n	<li>Check PRG pattern used</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Editing entities\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Test model is populated from repository</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Updating entities\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check that all model values are passed to the repository method</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Deleting entries\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check that all model values are passed to the repository method</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCheck out "all controller test"', '', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '104-revision-5', '', '', '2010-05-14 16:58:38', '2010-05-14 15:58:38', '', 104, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/14/104-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(137, 1, '2010-06-27 22:01:01', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<h2>Setting up LAMP on Ubuntu</h2>\nI want to be able to work on my blog code using myÂ net-book which is currently running Ubuntu (10.04 Lucid Lynx), so I need to get Apache, MySQL, and PHP working. It just takes a few simple steps.\n<ul>\n	<li>Install Apache2 using "sudo apt-get" (go to http://localhost/ to test)</li>\n	<li>Install PHP "sudo apt-get install php5 libapache2-mod-php5"</li>\n	<li>Test PHP by adding /var/www/testphp.php containing &lt;?php phpinfo(); ?&gt;</li>\n	<li>Install MySQL server "sudo apt-get install mysql-server"</li>\n	<li>Install MySQL Administrator (I used the Ubuntu Software Centre)</li>\n</ul>\nNext, create a new site configuration so that Apache can access my website files which are in /home/myusername/Desktop/myblog. This makes it easier to work with the website files as the default Apache site location has higher security restrictions. See the <a title="ApacheMySQLPHP Virtual Hosts" href="https://help.ubuntu.com/community/ApacheMySQLPHP#Virtual Hosts">Ubuntu Documentation</a> for instructions.\n\nSide note on UbuntuÂ terminal commands:\n<ul>\n	<li>the "sudo" command gives you root privileges to run a program</li>\n	<li>"apt-get" will download and install software packages</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>References</h2>\n<a href="http://www.howtoforge.com/ubuntu_lamp_for_newbies">http://www.howtoforge.com/ubuntu_lamp_for_newbies</a>\n\n<a href="https://help.ubuntu.com/community/ApacheMySQLPHP#Virtual Hosts">https://help.ubuntu.com/community/ApacheMySQLPHP#Virtual Hosts</a>', 'Developing my Blog', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2010-06-27 22:01:01', '2010-06-27 21:01:01', '', 0, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=137', 0, 'post', '', 0),
