(187, 1, '2010-08-05 12:58:21', '2010-08-05 11:58:21', '<h3>Core Commands</h3>\n<strong>git status</strong>\n\nUse to see the status of the files an the current branch. Use <strong>git diff</strong> to get more details.\n\n<strong>git add</strong>\n\nStages files to beÂ committed. Remember that if you stage a file, then edit it, you need to stage it again for the latest edit to be committed. Use <strong>-A</strong> to stage all.\n\n<strong>git diff</strong>\n\nIf you have changed a staged file, use diff to see the details. UseÂ <strong>â€“-staged<span style="font-weight: normal;"> or </span>--cached<span style="font-weight: normal;"> to see the staged differences.</span></strong>\n\n<strong>git commit</strong>\n\nCommit staged changes to local repository. Use the <strong>-a</strong> options to commit unstaged changes (to tracked files)\n\n<strong>git rm</strong>\n\nRemoved a file from the staging area, and also from the working directory if it exists there. Use <strong>git rm --cached </strong>to remove a file from the staging area.\n\n<strong>gitk</strong>\n\nVisual log history.\n<h3>Undoing Things</h3>\n<strong>git checkout [file]</strong>\n\n<strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">Checks out a file overwriting any local changes. Use </span></strong><strong>git checkout . </strong>to lose all local changes.\n\n<strong></strong><strong>git reset HEAD [files]</strong>\n\nRemoves files from the staging area.\n\n<strong>git reset [hash]</strong>\n\nReset the current head to the specified state.\n\n<strong>git reset --hard</strong>\n\nMatches the working tree and index to that of the tree being switched to, losing staged changes.\n<h3>Working with Branches</h3>\n<strong>git branch</strong>\n\nLists your local branches, use <strong>git branch -r</strong> to list the remote branches.\n\n<strong>git checkout </strong><strong><em>branch</em></strong>\n\nCheckout a branch to the working directory.\n<h3>Merging</h3>\n<strong>git merge [hash]</strong>\n\nMerge a commit from another branch.\n<div><strong>git checkout master</strong></div>\n<div><strong>git merge beta</strong></div>\n<div><strong>git push origin master</strong></div>\n<div>Merge beta branch into master branch</div>\n<h3>Working with Remotes</h3>\n<strong>git remote show [remote-name]</strong>\n\nGet the details of the remote repository, including branches.\n\n<strong>git remote</strong>\n\nLists your remote repositories.\n\n<strong>git fetch [remote-name]</strong>\n\nFetch changes from remote repository, but don''t update the working directory (use <strong>rebase </strong>for that).\n\n<strong>git pull [remote-name]</strong>\n\nFetch changes from remote repository and update the working directory.\n\n<strong>git push [remote-name] [branch-name]</strong>\n\nPush your local commits to a remote repository.\n\n<strong>Tricks</strong>\n\n<strong>git update-index</strong> --assume-unchanged connectionString.config\n\nIgnore a tracked file\n\n<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Useful References</span></strong>\n\n<a href="http://cheat.errtheblog.com/s/git">http://cheat.errtheblog.com/s/git</a>', 'Git Shortcuts', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '115-revision-10', '', '', '2010-08-05 12:58:21', '2010-08-05 11:58:21', '', 115, 'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/08/05/115-revision-10/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
