-nav-markup-in-firebug" src="http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/primary-nav-markup-in-firebug-600x430.jpg" alt="Firebug shows the markup of the navigation lists" width="600" height="430" />\r\n\r\nNext it''s just a matter of applying some css style to get the menu looking and behaving a bit more like a menu. I''ve wrapped the PageTree control with a div element with an id of "priary-nav" so I can target it with css rules.\r\n<pre class="brush:css">div#primary-nav ul\r\n{\r\n	list-style-image: none;\r\n	list-style-position: outside;\r\n	list-style-type: none;\r\n	margin: 0;\r\n	padding: 0;\r\n	text-align:center;\r\n}\r\n	div#primary-nav li\r\n	{\r\n		float: left;\r\n		background-color: #ccc;\r\n		width:100px;\r\n		text-align:center;\r\n	}\r\n		div#primary-nav li a\r\n		{\r\n			padding:5px;\r\n			display:block;\r\n		}\r\n\r\ndiv#primary-nav li ul\r\n{\r\n	width:100px;\r\n	position: absolute;\r\n	left: -999em;\r\n}\r\n	div#primary-nav li ul li\r\n	{\r\n		background-color: #eee;\r\n	}\r\n\r\ndiv#primary-nav li:hover ul\r\n{\r\n	left: auto;\r\n}</pre>\r\nAnd with style applied the menu looks like this:\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-176" title="primary-navigation-with-css" src="http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/primary-navigation-with-css.jpg" alt="The navigation menu with css rules applied" width="369" height="207" />\r\n\r\nBuilding on this example should enable me to quickly build drop-down menus for a number of scenarios - there are a lot more properties and templates of the PageTree control to explore, and understanding the basics is the first step to building more complex navigation to fit the requirements of a specific site.\r\n\r\nUseful links:\r\n\r\nhttp://www.frederikvig.com/tag/episerver-web-controls/', 'EPiServer PageTree for primary navigation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '170-revision-8', '', '', '2010-08-22 08:34:23', '2010-08-22 07:34:23', '', 170, 'http://localhost/jsewell_mywordpressblog/index.php/2010/08/22/170-revision-8/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
